*MAC MINI AGENT SERVER*

*ADR-033 — Operator Dashboard Metrics Framework*

*Status: DECIDED*

Date: March 29, 2026

Phase: Pre-Phase 1  |  Architecture Complete — v2.9

Owner: Sheldon Wheeler

*ADR Coverage:  AC · AU · CM · IA · IR · SA · SC · SI*

NIST 800-53 Alignment:  ADR-032

# **1.  Context and Decision**

The operator has identified a need for a structured, visual monitoring framework spanning infrastructure, agent behavior, security posture, and compliance status. The architecture decisions recorded in ADR-001 through ADR-032 produce observable events and metrics at every layer of the stack. This ADR formalizes which metrics are collected, how they are displayed, and when they become available (Phase 1 vs Phase 2).

Decision: Adopt a layered Operator Dashboard Metrics Framework organized into four domains: Infrastructure, Agent Layer, Approval and Workflow, and Security and Compliance. Phase 1 metrics are available from setup day using native macOS tooling and direct PostgreSQL queries. Phase 2 metrics are delivered by the compliance_monitor sub-agent (ADR-032) via scheduled Telegram reports.

This ADR supersedes no prior ADR. It extends ADR-029 (audit table), ADR-031 (scheduled reviews), and ADR-032 (NIST compliance monitoring) by defining the full observable metric surface and display format recommendations.

