| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| web-search-local | Research | Custom — Brave API + Tier 1 Ollama summarizer | Raw results summarized locally before context injection. Max 200–400 tokens per call. Max 5 results. Max 3 queries/session without operator approval. | Phase 1 — build at stack setup |
| security-check | — | Community (ClawHub) — evaluated Session 10 | — | Rejected — manual source review and minimal community skill footprint make runtime scanning unnecessary |
| domain-trust-check | — | Community (ClawHub) — evaluated Session 10 | — | Rejected — scrape targets are fixed curated government URLs, not dynamic untrusted sources |

*No community skill may be installed without explicit operator approval. Build-local-first and token conservation principles adopted March 30, 2026.*

# **12.  Visual Reference — Dashboard Display Examples**

This section was merged from the standalone Dashboard Metrics Visual Reference document (March 30, 2026). It provides concrete display format examples, example data values, SQL implementation notes, and the phased implementation roadmap. All examples use illustrative data — not live production values.

## **12.1  System Status At-a-Glance**

The Telegram-accessible system status summary. Traffic lights represent binary OK / warning / critical states. Sparklines show 24-hour trends. Badges show current instantaneous values.

*Traffic Light Status Board — Infrastructure*

Format: Three-state indicator. Green = nominal. Yellow = warning threshold crossed. Red = critical — immediate action required. These are the first items checked in any operator review session.

| **Metric** | **Green** | **Yellow** | **Red** | **Target State** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Thermal Pressure | Nominal | Fair | Serious / Critical | Nominal |
| Memory Pressure | < 85% used | 85–93% used | > 93% / swap active | Nominal |
| Swap Usage | Zero | < 1 GB | > 1 GB | Nominal |
| WireGuard Tunnel | Connected | Reconnecting | Down > 5 min | Nominal |
| OpenClaw Daemon | Running | Restart in progress | Down > 2 min | Nominal |
| Telegram Connection | Connected | Reconnecting | Down > 5 min | Nominal |
| Backup Last Run | Success < 24h | Success > 24h | Failed | Nominal |
| FileVault Encryption | Enabled | — | Disabled | Nominal |
| Opus Usage (Phase 1) | Zero calls | — | Any Opus call | Nominal |
| Policy Violations | Zero | — | Any violation | Nominal |
| Prompt Injection | Zero detections | — | Any detection | Nominal |

*Sparklines — Hardware Thermals (24-Hour Rolling)*

Format: Compact trend over the last 24 hours. Current value badge on right. Alert threshold shown for reference. Delivered via Stats (mac-stats.com) menu bar or Telegram query.

| **Metric** | **Current (Example)** | **Alert Threshold** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| CPU Temperature | 54 °C | Alert: > 85 °C |
| GPU Temperature | 41 °C | Alert: > 80 °C |
| System Power Draw | 17 W | Alert: > 80 W |
| Fan Speed | 1,200 RPM | Alert: > 3,000 RPM |

*3-Number Badge Rows — Rolling Volume Summary*

Format: Three rolling-window badges per metric (Today / 7-Day / 30-Day). Designed for Telegram query response.

| **Metric** | **Today** | **7-Day** | **30-Day** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Total Agent Actions | 47 actions | 312 actions | 1,247 actions |
| Estimated API Spend | $0.23 | $1.84 | $7.62 |
| Circuit Breaker Hits | 0 | 2 | 5 |
| Opus Usage (Phase 1 target: 0) | 0 ✓ | 0 ✓ | 0 ✓ |
| Pending Approvals | 2 open | — | — |
| Backup Last Run (Age) | 6h 14m ago ✓ | 7 / 7 success | 30 / 30 success |
| Auto-NO Timeouts | 0 | 1 | 3 |

## **12.2  Routing and Tier Distribution**

*Tier Call Distribution — Proportional Bar*

Format: Proportional horizontal bar. Width represents percentage share. Color-coded by tier. Phase 1 goal: Tier 4 (Opus) = 0% at all times. A rising Tier 3 percentage signals confidence threshold recalibration may be needed.

| **Tier** | **Description** | **Share (Example)** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Tier 1 | Local 7B (Ollama) — Simple tasks | 52% |
| Tier 2 | Local 14B / 32B (Ollama) — Moderate tasks | 34% |
| Tier 3 | Cloud Sonnet (OpenRouter) — Complex tasks | 14% |
| Tier 4 | Cloud Opus (OpenRouter) — Phase 1: BLOCKED | 0% |

*Persona Activity — Stacked Bar by Day (7-Day Example)*

Format: Stacked bar chart. Each bar = one day. Segments = Prototype / Automate / Research. Mismatched patterns between personas may signal a miscalibrated agent.

| **Persona** | **Mon** | **Tue** | **Wed** | **Thu** | **Fri** | **Sat** | **Sun** | **7-Day Total** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Prototype | 18 | 22 | 15 | 24 | 19 | 8 | 6 | 112 |
| Automate | 12 | 14 | 11 | 16 | 13 | 5 | 4 | 75 |
| Research | 8 | 10 | 7 | 11 | 9 | 4 | 3 | 52 |
| Daily Total | 38 | 46 | 33 | 51 | 41 | 17 | 13 | 239 |

## **12.3  Actions Per Hour Heatmap**

Format: 7-day rolling heatmap. Rows = day of week. Columns = hour (0–23). Color intensity = action count. Cells in quiet hours columns (19–23 and 0–6) should always be empty. Any non-empty quiet hours cell = investigate immediately.

Color scale: 0 actions = white · 1–2 = light · 3–4 = medium · 5–6 = dark · 7+ = darkest · Quiet hours violation = red.

Example reading: Peak activity concentrated 9am–4pm weekdays. Quiet hours columns clean. Weekend volume lighter but consistent. This is the target pattern.

| **Day** | **Peak Hour Range** | **Peak Count** | **Quiet Hours Clean** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Monday | 09:00–16:00 | 6 actions/hr | Yes |
| Tuesday | 09:00–16:00 | 7 actions/hr | Yes |
| Wednesday | 09:00–16:00 | 5 actions/hr | Yes |
| Thursday | 09:00–16:00 | 8 actions/hr | Yes |
| Friday | 09:00–16:00 | 6 actions/hr | Yes |
| Saturday | 09:00–15:00 | 3 actions/hr | Yes |
| Sunday | 09:00–13:00 | 2 actions/hr | Yes |

SQL: SELECT DATE_PART('hour', created_at) AS hour, DATE_PART('dow', created_at) AS dow, COUNT(*) FROM agent_actions WHERE created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '7 days' GROUP BY hour, dow ORDER BY dow, hour;

## **12.4  Irreversibility Score Distribution**

Format: Horizontal bar histogram. Each bucket = a range of irreversibility scores. Approval gate triggers at score > 20 (ADR-028). A healthy distribution shows the vast majority of actions well below 20, with a small tail in the 15–20 range.

| **Score Range** | **Description** | **Count (Example)** | **% of Total** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 0–4 | Read-only / informational | 510 | 41% |
| 5–9 | Low-risk write | 380 | 30% |
| 10–14 | Moderate write | 220 | 18% |
| 15–19 | Approaching threshold | 110 | 9% |
| 20–29 | Approval required | 25 | 2% |
| 30+ | High-consequence action | 5 | 0% |

Signal interpretation: If the 20–29 and 30+ buckets are growing over time, recalibrate the task classification table (ADR-018). If the 15–19 bucket is large, many actions are near threshold — review whether they should be classified higher.

SQL: SELECT WIDTH_BUCKET(irreversibility_score, 0, 40, 8) AS bucket, COUNT(*) FROM agent_actions WHERE created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days' GROUP BY bucket ORDER BY bucket;

## **12.5  Approval Workflow Status**

*Pending Approvals Queue*

Format: Table with age indicator. Each row = one open approval request. Color-coded by age relative to the 30-minute auto-NO timeout. Actions approaching timeout highlighted.

| **Persona** | **Action Description** | **Irrev. Score** | **Age** | **Timeout In** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Prototype | Write report to /outputs/Q1_brief.md | 24 — Approval required | 8 min | 22 min remaining |
| Automate | Execute shell command: npm run build | 31 — Approval required | 22 min | 8 min remaining ⚠ |

SQL: SELECT agent_persona, action_description, irreversibility_score, created_at, NOW() - created_at AS age FROM agent_actions WHERE approval_status = 'pending' ORDER BY created_at ASC;

*7-Day Backup Status Grid*

Format: One cell per day. Green = successful backup. Red = backup failure (also triggers Telegram alert via ADR-019). Goal: 7 consecutive successful runs.

| **Run** | **Mon** | **Tue** | **Wed** | **Thu** | **Fri** | **Sat** | **Sun** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Status | OK | OK | OK | OK | OK | OK | OK |
| Duration | 1m 12s | 1m 08s | 1m 15s | 1m 11s | 1m 18s | 1m 09s | 1m 14s |
| Dump Size | 142 MB | 143 MB | 144 MB | 144 MB | 145 MB | 145 MB | 146 MB |

